From cou.: 11 The model is implemented in the ESPResSo molecular dynamics simulation package.54 For computational convenience the implementation is done using reduced units, i.e. we chose suitable units of length, mass and energy and express all quantities as multiples of these units. The unit of mass is m ≈ 8 × 10−26 kg, of energy is ε = 8.6 × 10−21J = 1.2 kcal mol−1 = 2kBT and of length is σ ≈ 4.0 Å as described elsewhere.31 It follows that our unit of temperature is ε/kB, where kB is the Boltzmann constant. The unit of time τ is estimated by equating the diffusion coefficient of cholate ions (5 × 10−10 m2 s−1)55 to the diffusion coefficient of monomers (0.04σ2/τ) from our simulation at the lowest concentration here tested. We find τ ≈ 12 ps. We note that this value represents only a coarse estimate of the unit of time, so in this work we focus on understanding the relative dynamics of the various processes involved in changes of micelle size and the sequence of events involved in such processes. The trends seen in the simulations are thus directly comparable to experiment despite the uncertainty in our estimate of τ.
From Soup: 11 The model is implemented in the ESPResSo molecular dynamics simulation package. 54 For computational convenience the implementation is done using reduced units, i.e. we chose suitable units of length, mass and energy and express all quantities as multiples of these units. The unit of mass is m ≈ 8 × 10 −26 kg, of energy is ε = 8.6 × 10 −21 J = 1.2 kcal mol −1 = 2 k B T and of length is σ ≈ 4.0 Å as described elsewhere. 31 It follows that our unit of temperature is ε / k B , where k B is the Boltzmann constant. The unit of time τ is estimated by equating the diffusion coefficient of cholate ions (5 × 10 −10 m 2 s −1 ) 55 to the diffusion coefficient of monomers (0.04 σ 2 / τ ) from our simulation at the lowest concentration here tested. We find τ ≈ 12 ps. We note that this value represents only a coarse estimate of the unit of time, so in this work we focus on understanding the relative dynamics of the various processes involved in changes of micelle size and the sequence of events involved in such processes. The trends seen in the simulations are thus directly comparable to experiment despite the uncertainty in our estimate of τ .
