From cou.: 26 To evaluate which processes contribute most to changes in micellar size we calculate the reaction rates, λ, for addition and removal of monomers and larger fragments. Fission and fusion events are described by quasichemical reactionswhere An refers to a cluster with aggregation number n, or a monomer if n = 1. For convenience, in what follows n is the size (i.e. aggregation number) of the initial micelle (or monomer) whereas m is the size of the fissioned or fusioned fragment. The rate constants for fusion (k+) and fission (k−) are related to the reaction rates according to the well-known expressionswith Cn the number density of micelles with aggregation number n.
